    <p class="muted">
      * Llama models use Meta's community license. It's free for this kind of use, but requires
      the “Built with Llama” attribution – Cardo shows it for you where the model is active.
      <br />
      ** Gemma models are covered by Google's own Gemma Terms of Use rather than a classic
      open-source license. Cardo shows you the terms and asks for your consent <em>before</em>
      the download starts – never after. Everything else in the table is Apache-2.0 or MIT:
      no strings attached.
    </p>

    <h3>Rule of thumb by machine</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>8 GB laptop:</strong> Qwen3 0.6B–4B, Llama 3.2 1B/3B, Phi-4-mini or Gemma 3 4B.
        Qwen3 4B is the usual recommendation; if it feels sluggish, drop to 1.7B – a fast small
        model beats a slow big one every day.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>16 GB:</strong> Qwen3 8B, Llama 3.1 8B, Mistral 7B, Granite 8B or DeepSeek-R1 7B
        run comfortably. Gemma 3 12B and the 14B models fit, but they're the upper edge –
        expect them to take their time.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>32 GB and up:</strong> everything above, plus Qwen3 14B/30B-A3B, Mistral Small
        24B and Gemma 3 27B. Here quality is the only question – pick by strengths, not by fit.
      </li>
